On July 6, 2012, the President signed into law H.R. 4348, also known as the "Moving Ahead for Progress in the 21st Century Act" or "MAP-21". This law reauthorizes taxes that support the Highway Trust Fund until September 30, 2016, and grants authority to spend from that Fund until September 30, 2014. It also introduces significant reforms to surface transportation programs. Additionally, the law reauthorizes the National Flood Insurance Program (NFIP) until September 30, 2017, and implements major reforms to the NFIP. Lastly, it extends the current interest rate of 3.4 percent on new subsidized Federal Direct Stafford Loans for undergraduate students until July 1, 2013.